#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""YouTube source management CLI — Phase 2.

Usage:
    csf-source add <channel_url_or_playlist_url>  # Initial import: full API pagination
    csf-source list                               # List all tracked sources
    csf-source check <source_id>                  # Daily check: RSS → gap detection → API if needed
    csf-source sync <source_id>                   # Process all pending videos via batch
    csf-source fetch [--source <url>]             # ESCALATION: fetch transcripts (yt-dlp → Selenium)
    csf-source history                            # Extract channels from YouTube watch history and add new ones

Commands:
    add       Add a new channel or playlist source. For channels, resolves the uploads
              playlist ID via API and enumerates all videos. For playlists, enumerates
              all videos directly. Marks all videos as pending in batch_status.

    list      List all tracked sources from channel_metadata table, showing:
              - channel_url, playlist_id, video_count_estimate, last_checked

    check     Run daily check for a specific source:
              1. RSS feed for recent ~15-20 videos
              2. Gap detection: if RSS shows ≥15 non-overlapping AND newest batch > 7 days
              3. API gap resolution if gap detected
              4. Marks new videos as pending

    sync      Process all pending videos for a source via batch.analyze_videos_parallel().
              Does NOT check for new videos — use 'check' first.

    fetch     ESCALATION BATCH PROCESS: Fetch transcripts for pending videos using
              yt-dlp → Selenium fallback chain. This is the RECOMMENDED way to download
              transcripts in bulk. Handles retries, caching, and status updates automatically.
              --source <url>   Process only this channel URL (default: all channels)
              --dry-run        Show what would be fetched without fetching
              --workers <n>    Number of parallel workers (default: 1)
"""

